                },
                {
                    "title": "<span style=\"font-size:26px;\">Key points</span>",
                    "content": "<ul class=\"key-points\">\n<li>In more than 1 in 4 countries with comparable data, at least 5% of young women aged 18\u201329 reported experiences of sexual violence in childhood.</li>\n<li>While children of both sexes can be the target of sexual violence, girls are at a heightened risk. Girls are 4 to 5 times more likely than boys to experience sexual violence.</li>\n<li>There is a strong correlation between childhood sexual abuse and sexual abuse after age 15, which may suggest that among children, adolescent girls are at higher risk of experiencing sexual violence.</li>\n</ul>\n",
                    "contentActions": [],
                    "creaDate": 1603056272440,
                    "pubDate": 1603056272440,
                    "status": "PUBLISHED",
                    "media": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "image": {
                            "url": "https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/content/items/1dc2ad5ad619470ba1e998dcfc71db0a/resources/anh-nguyen-v-NBXj3Yv5o-unsplash__1603056270918__w1200.jpg",
                            "type": "image",
                            "altText": "",
                            "sizes": [
                                {
                                    "name": "anh-nguyen-v-NBXj3Yv5o-unsplash__1603056270918__w1200.jpg",
                                    "url": "https://www.arcgis.com/sharing/rest/content/items/1dc2ad5ad619470ba1e998dcfc71db0a/resources/anh-nguyen-v-NBXj3Yv5o-unsplash__1603056270918__w1200.jpg",
                                    "width": 1200
                                }
                            ],
                            "display": "fill"
                        }
